hybrid_logic_lean_revisited

This repository continues and completes Alex Oltean's Lean 4 formalization of
hybrid logic:

    Original:  https://github.com/alexoltean61/hybrid_logic_lean
    This work: https://github.com/catskillsresearch/hybrid_logic_lean_revisited

The code under Hybrid/ originates with Alex Oltean and follows
Patrick Blackburn, "Hybrid Completeness", Logic Journal of the IGPL, 1998.
That original work was published upstream without an explicit license; all
rights to it remain with its author. It is included and modified here in good
faith for non-commercial academic research, with attribution, and no rights
over the original work are claimed.

The modifications in this repository -- porting to Lean v4.30.0 / mathlib
v4.30.0 and completing the completeness proof -- together with the new files at
the repository root, are contributed under the Apache License, Version 2.0, to
the extent they are separable from the original work.

The disjoint-sum (N ⊕ ℕ) Henkin construction used to close the completeness
proof was suggested by Bud Mishra.
